<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Velvet Knowledge Hub — Korea deer velvet trade intelligence</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/style.css">
  <style>
    /* ── C-8 additions ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

    /* CSS variables — new toggle tokens */
    :root {
      --toggle-radius:       4px;
      --toggle-bg:           var(--surface);
      --toggle-active-bg:    var(--text-primary);
      --toggle-active-text:  #ffffff;
    }

    /* Segmented control (monthly/annual) */
    .segmented-control {
      display: inline-flex;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--toggle-radius);
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .segmented-control button {
      padding: 5px 14px;
      font-size: 0.8125rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
      background: var(--toggle-bg);
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      border: none;
      border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: background 0.12s ease, color 0.12s ease;
    }

    .segmented-control button:last-child {
      border-right: none;
    }

    .segmented-control button[aria-pressed="true"] {
      background: var(--toggle-active-bg);
      color: var(--toggle-active-text);
    }

    /* Toggle row for A1/A2 charts */
    .chart-toggle-row {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 10px;
      margin-bottom: 14px;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .chart-toggle-row label {
      font-size: 0.8125rem;
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      white-space: nowrap;
    }

    .chart-toggle-row select,
    .chart-toggle-row input[type="month"] {
      font-size: 0.8125rem;
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
      padding: 4px 8px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text-primary);
    }

    .chart-toggle-row select:focus,
    .chart-toggle-row input[type="month"]:focus {
      outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
      outline-offset: 1px;
    }

    .chart-toggle-row .toggle-group {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 6px;
    }

    /* Section B placeholder */
    .analysis-placeholder {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 8px;
      padding: 24px 20px;
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px dashed var(--border);
      border-left: 3px solid var(--border);
    }

    .analysis-placeholder__title {
      font-size: 0.9375rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    .analysis-placeholder__body {
      font-size: 0.8125rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      line-height: 1.6;
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    /* Section C reference accordion */
    .reference-accordion {
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    }

    .reference-accordion summary {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 14px 16px;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-size: 0.9375rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
      list-style: none;
      user-select: none;
    }

    .reference-accordion summary::-webkit-details-marker {
      display: none;
    }

    .reference-accordion summary::after {
      content: "\25B6";
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      transition: transform 0.15s ease;
    }

    details[open].reference-accordion summary::after {
      transform: rotate(90deg);
    }

    .reference-accordion__body {
      padding: 16px 16px 20px;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    }

    .reference-accordion__body p {
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.65;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    .reference-accordion__body ul {
      padding-left: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    .reference-accordion__body li {
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.55;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    .reference-download-link {
      display: inline-block;
      font-size: 0.875rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--accent);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    .reference-download-link:hover {
      color: var(--text-primary);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    /* Section D — CSV email form */
    .csv-email-form {
      display: none;
      gap: 8px;
      align-items: center;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .csv-email-form.is-visible {
      display: flex;
    }

    .csv-email-input {
      font-size: 0.8125rem;
      padding: 5px 10px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      color: var(--text-primary);
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
      min-width: 220px;
      flex: 1;
    }

    .csv-email-input:focus {
      outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
      outline-offset: 1px;
    }

    .csv-send-btn {
      font-size: 0.8125rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      padding: 5px 14px;
      background: var(--accent);
      color: #fff;
      border: none;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    .csv-send-btn:hover {
      background: var(--text-primary);
    }

    .csv-cancel-btn {
      font-size: 0.8125rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      background: transparent;
      border: none;
      cursor: pointer;
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 2px;
    }

    .csv-confirmation {
      display: none;
      font-size: 0.8125rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-style: italic;
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    .csv-confirmation.is-visible {
      display: block;
    }

    .csv-error {
      display: none;
      font-size: 0.8125rem;
      color: var(--delta-negative);
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
      margin-top: 4px;
    }

    .csv-error.is-visible {
      display: block;
    }

    /* Article thumbnail — C-8 update */
    .article-thumbnail {
      width: 80px;
      height: 60px;
      object-fit: cover;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      display: block;
    }

    /* ── C-8 responsive ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .chart-toggle-row {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: stretch;
      }

      .chart-toggle-row select,
      .chart-toggle-row input[type="month"] {
        width: 100%;
      }

      .chart-toggle-row .toggle-group {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: flex-start;
      }

      .table-controls {
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: stretch;
        gap: 8px;
      }

      .csv-email-form {
        flex-direction: column;
      }

      .csv-email-input {
        min-width: 0;
        width: 100%;
      }

      /* Thumbnail: smaller on mobile */
      .article-thumbnail {
        width: 64px;
        height: 48px;
      }
    }

    @media (max-width: 480px) {
      /* Segmented control degrades to a select at narrowest widths.
         The HTML includes both; JS swaps which is visible. */
      .segmented-control {
        display: none;
      }

      .segmented-select {
        display: block;
      }

      /* Thumbnail: hide entirely at narrowest widths */
      .article-thumbnail {
        display: none;
      }
    }

    /* At wider widths the select fallback is hidden (JS shows/hides segmented). */
    .segmented-select {
      display: none;
    }

    /* Date range note */
    .date-range-note {
      font-size: 0.75rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      margin-left: 4px;
    }

    /* M3/R1 — sticky nav tab bar */
    nav.page-wrapper {
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      background: var(--bg);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      z-index: 100;
      padding-top: 8px;
      padding-bottom: 8px;
    }

    nav.section-nav a.is-active {
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
      color: var(--accent);
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    /* N2 — iOS-style T12M toggle switch */
    .toggle-switch-row {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 8px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      font-size: 0.8125rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-family: "Trebuchet MS", "Gill Sans MT", "Gill Sans", "Century Gothic", Arial, sans-serif;
    }
    .toggle-switch {
      position: relative;
      width: 36px;
      height: 20px;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    .toggle-switch input {
      opacity: 0;
      width: 0;
      height: 0;
      position: absolute;
    }
    .toggle-slider {
      position: absolute;
      inset: 0;
      background: var(--border);
      border-radius: 20px;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: background 0.2s;
    }
    .toggle-slider::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      width: 14px;
      height: 14px;
      left: 3px;
      top: 3px;
      background: #fff;
      border-radius: 50%;
      transition: transform 0.2s;
    }
    .toggle-switch input:checked + .toggle-slider {
      background: var(--accent);
    }
    .toggle-switch input:checked + .toggle-slider::before {
      transform: translateX(16px);
    }

    /* ── C-8 print rules ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
    @media print {
      .chart-toggle-row { display: none; }
      .toggle-switch-row { display: none; }
      .segmented-control { display: none; }
      .segmented-select { display: none; }

      .analysis-placeholder {
        border: 1px solid #999;
        border-left: 3px solid #999;
      }

      details.reference-accordion {
        border-left: 3px solid #888;
      }

      details.reference-accordion > .reference-accordion__body {
        display: block !important;
      }

      .table-controls,
      .csv-email-form,
      .csv-confirmation {
        display: none;
      }

      .import-records-table tbody tr {
        display: table-row !important;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

{# ── HEADER ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<header>
  <div class="page-wrapper">
    <h1>Velvet Knowledge Hub</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Korea deer velvet market intelligence for the New Zealand deer industry</p>
    <p class="last-built caption">Last built: {{ meta.last_built_utc | default(build_date) | default("—") }}</p>
    <a class="pdf-download-btn" href="velvet-knowledge-hub.pdf" download>Download PDF</a>
  </div>
</header>

{# ── KPI STRIP ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<div class="page-wrapper">
  <div class="kpi-strip">

    <div class="kpi-card">
      <p class="kpi-label">KOREA IMPORTS (ROLLING 12 MONTHS)</p>
      {% if kpi is defined and kpi.qia_rolling12m_kg is defined and kpi.qia_rolling12m_kg != "—" %}
        <p class="kpi-value">{{ kpi.qia_rolling12m_kg }} <span class="kpi-unit">kg</span></p>
        {% if kpi.qia_rolling12m_date_start != "—" %}
          <p class="delta-indicator delta-neutral">{{ kpi.qia_rolling12m_date_start }} – {{ kpi.qia_rolling12m_date_end }}</p>
        {% endif %}
        {% if kpi.qia_yoy_label != "—" %}
          <p class="delta-indicator">{{ kpi.qia_yoy_label }}</p>
        {% endif %}
        <p class="delta-indicator delta-neutral">dried-equivalent — QIA</p>
      {% else %}
        <p class="kpi-value text-muted">—</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>

    <div class="kpi-card">
      <p class="kpi-label">NEWS ARTICLES (LAST 90 DAYS)</p>
      {% if kpi is defined and kpi.articles_90d is defined and kpi.articles_90d != "—" %}
        <p class="kpi-value">{{ kpi.articles_90d }} <span class="kpi-unit">articles</span></p>
        <p class="delta-indicator delta-neutral">relevant articles — Naver + Google News</p>
      {% else %}
        <p class="kpi-value text-muted">—</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>

    <div class="kpi-card">
      <p class="kpi-label">FOOD IMPORTS (LAST 90 DAYS)</p>
      {% if kpi is defined and kpi.food_imports_90d is defined and kpi.food_imports_90d != "—" %}
        <p class="kpi-value">{{ kpi.food_imports_90d }} <span class="kpi-unit">declarations</span></p>
        <p class="delta-indicator delta-neutral">MFDS food safety import declarations for velvet (food channel only, not pharmaceutical)</p>
      {% else %}
        <p class="kpi-value text-muted">—</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>

  </div>
</div>

{# ── NAVIGATION ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<nav class="page-wrapper section-nav" aria-label="Dashboard sections">
  <ul class="nav-list">
    <li><a href="#section-1">1. Basic trade statistics</a></li>
    <li><a href="#section-2">2. News pulse</a></li>
    <li><a href="#section-3">3. Import intelligence</a></li>
    <li><a href="#section-4">4. Import records</a></li>
    <li><a href="#section-5">5. Trade reference</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>

{# ── MAIN CONTENT ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── #}
<main class="page-wrapper">

  {# ── SECTION 1 — BASIC TRADE STATISTICS ──────────────────────────────── #}
  <section id="section-1">

    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-header-left">
        <h2>1. Basic trade statistics</h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    {# ── A1 — Korea import volume (QIA) ──────────────────────────────────── #}
    <div id="a1-panel">

      <h2 style="font-size:1.125rem; margin-top:24px; margin-bottom:4px; padding-top:10px;">Korea import volume</h2>
      <p class="source-footnote" style="margin-top:4px; border-top:none; padding-top:0;">Source: Korea Animal and Plant Quarantine Agency (QIA) — import inspection records.</p>

      {% set trade_flows = sections.trade_flows if sections is defined and sections.trade_flows is defined else {} %}
      {% if trade_flows.enabled and trade_flows.has_data %}

        {# Toggle row #}
        <div class="chart-toggle-row" id="a1-toggle-row" style="margin-top:12px;">
          <div class="toggle-group">
            {# Segmented control — monthly/annual #}
            <div class="segmented-control" id="a1-seg" role="group" aria-label="View period">
              <button type="button" aria-pressed="true" data-view="monthly" onclick="a1SetView('monthly',this)">Monthly</button>
              <button type="button" aria-pressed="false" data-view="annual" onclick="a1SetView('annual',this)">Annual summary</button>
            </div>
            {# Select fallback for ≤480px — JS syncs value with segmented control #}
            <select class="segmented-select" id="a1-seg-select" onchange="a1SetViewFromSelect(this)">
              <option value="monthly">Monthly</option>
              <option value="annual">Annual summary</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="toggle-group">
            <label for="a1-from">From</label>
            <input type="month" id="a1-from" onchange="a1Render()">
            <label for="a1-to">To</label>
            <input type="month" id="a1-to" onchange="a1Render()">
            <span class="date-range-note">Data available from January 2021</span>
          </div>
          <div class="toggle-group">
            <label for="a1-country">Country</label>
            <select id="a1-country" onchange="a1Render()">
              <option value="">All countries</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="toggle-group">
            <label for="a1-form">Form</label>
            <select id="a1-form" onchange="a1Render()">
              <option value="">All forms</option>
              <option value="frozen">Fresh velvet</option>
              <option value="dried">Dried velvet</option>
            </select>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chart-panel">
          <h3>Korea import volume — monthly and trailing 12 months</h3>
          {# N2: T12M toggle switch #}
          <div class="toggle-switch-row">
            <label class="toggle-switch">
              <input type="checkbox" id="a1-t12m-toggle" checked onchange="a1ToggleT12M(this)">
              <span class="toggle-slider"></span>
            </label>
            <span>12-month rolling total</span>
          </div>
          <div class="chart-canvas-wrapper" style="height:320px;">
            <canvas id="chart-a1" aria-label="Korea QIA import volume — monthly stacked bar and trailing 12-month line" role="img"></canvas>
          </div>
          <p class="chart-annotation">Frozen equivalent volume: dried velvet converted at ÷ 0.33 (1 kg dried = 3.03 kg frozen equivalent). Source: QIA import inspection records.</p>
        </div>

      {% else %}
        <div class="placeholder-card" style="margin-top:16px;">
          <p class="placeholder-title">Korea import volume data not yet available</p>
          <p class="placeholder-body">Data will appear after the next scheduled build.</p>
        </div>
      {% endif %}
    </div>{# /a1-panel #}

    {# ── A2 — NZ export volume (Stats NZ) ────────────────────────────────── #}
    <div id="a2-panel" style="margin-top:40px;">

      <h2 style="font-size:1.125rem; margin-top:0; margin-bottom:4px; border-top: 2px solid var(--accent); padding-top:10px;">NZ export volume</h2>
      <p class="source-footnote" style="margin-top:4px; border-top:none; padding-top:0;">Source: Stats NZ — overseas merchandise trade, deer velvet HS codes.</p>

      {% if trade_flows.enabled and trade_flows.has_data %}

        <div class="chart-toggle-row" id="a2-toggle-row" style="margin-top:12px;">
          <div class="toggle-group">
            <div class="segmented-control" id="a2-seg" role="group" aria-label="View period">
              <button type="button" aria-pressed="true" data-view="monthly" onclick="a2SetView('monthly',this)">Monthly</button>
              <button type="button" aria-pressed="false" data-view="annual" onclick="a2SetView('annual',this)">Annual summary</button>
            </div>
            <select class="segmented-select" id="a2-seg-select" onchange="a2SetViewFromSelect(this)">
              <option value="monthly">Monthly</option>
              <option value="annual">Annual summary</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="toggle-group">
            <label for="a2-from">From</label>
            <input type="month" id="a2-from" onchange="a2Render()">
            <label for="a2-to">To</label>
            <input type="month" id="a2-to" onchange="a2Render()">
            <span class="date-range-note">Data available from January 2021</span>
          </div>
          <div class="toggle-group">
            <label for="a2-country">Country</label>
            <select id="a2-country" onchange="a2Render()">
              <option value="">All countries</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="toggle-group">
            <label for="a2-form">HS code category</label>
            <select id="a2-form" onchange="a2Render()">
              <option value="">All forms</option>
              <option value="frozen">Fresh</option>
              <option value="dried">Dried</option>
            </select>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="chart-panel">
          <h3>NZ export volume — monthly and trailing 12 months</h3>
          {# N2: T12M toggle switch #}
          <div class="toggle-switch-row">
            <label class="toggle-switch">
              <input type="checkbox" id="a2-t12m-toggle" checked onchange="a2ToggleT12M(this)">
              <span class="toggle-slider"></span>
            </label>
            <span>12-month rolling total</span>
          </div>
          <div class="chart-canvas-wrapper" style="height:320px;">
            <canvas id="chart-a2" aria-label="NZ Stats NZ export volume — monthly stacked bar and trailing 12-month line" role="img"></canvas>
          </div>
          <p class="chart-annotation">Frozen equivalent volume: Stats NZ reports fresh and dried velvet separately under distinct HS codes. Dried velvet converted at ÷ 0.33 for comparability with A1.</p>
        </div>

      {% else %}
        <div class="placeholder-card" style="margin-top:16px;">
          <p class="placeholder-title">NZ export volume data not yet available</p>
          <p class="placeholder-body">Data will appear after the next scheduled build.</p>
        </div>
      {% endif %}
    </div>{# /a2-panel #}

    {# ── A3 — Korea import price (MFDS) ──────────────────────────────────── #}
    <div id="a3-panel" style="margin-top:40px;">

      <h2 style="font-size:1.125rem; margin-top:0; margin-bottom:4px; border-top: 2px solid var(--accent); padding-top:10px;">Korea import price</h2>
      <p class="source-footnote" style="margin-top:4px; border-top:none; padding-top:0;">Source: MFDS (Ministry of Food and Drug Safety, Korea) — 식품의약품통계연보 (Korean medicine yearbook), herbal medicine channel. Annual data.</p>

      {% if mfds_annual_series and mfds_annual_series.has_data %}
        <div class="chart-panel" style="margin-top:12px;">
          <h3>Average import price — Korean herbal medicine channel</h3>
          <p class="chart-scope-note">Herbal medicine channel only. Does not include food ingredient imports.</p>
          <div class="chart-canvas-wrapper" style="height:260px;">
            <canvas id="chart-a3" aria-label="MFDS annual average import price, Korean herbal medicine channel" role="img"></canvas>
          </div>
          <p class="chart-annotation">Source: MFDS 식품의약품통계연보 Table 6-3-8. Korean herbal medicine channel (pharmaceutical classification). Does not include food ingredient imports shown in the import records section below.</p>
        </div>
      {% else %}
        <div class="placeholder-card" style="margin-top:16px;">
          <p class="placeholder-title">Korea import price data not yet available</p>
          <p class="placeholder-body">MFDS annual herbal medicine channel data will appear after the next scheduled build.</p>
        </div>
      {% endif %}

    </div>{# /a3-panel #}

  </section>

  {# ── SECTION 2 — NEWS PULSE ───────────────────────────────────────────── #}
  {% set news_pulse = sections.news_pulse if sections is defined and sections.news_pulse is defined else {} %}
  <section id="section-2">

    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-header-left">
        <h2>2. News pulse</h2>
        <span class="last-updated">Last updated: {{ news_pulse.last_updated | default("—") }}</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="source-footnote">Korean media articles matching the velvet keyword, classified and summarised by AI. Showing relevant articles from the last 90 days.</p>

    {% if news_pulse.enabled and news_pulse.has_data %}

      {% set publishable = [] %}
      {% for row in news_pulse.data %}
        {% if row.include_on_site | string | upper in ("TRUE", "1", "YES") and row.published_date | string >= cutoff_90d %}
          {% set _ = publishable.append(row) %}
        {% endif %}
      {% endfor %}

      {% if publishable %}
        <p class="article-list-header">{{ publishable | length }} relevant article{{ 's' if publishable | length != 1 else '' }} — last 90 days</p>
        <ul class="article-list" aria-label="Korea deer velvet relevant articles — last 90 days">
          {% for article in publishable %}
            {# Column-swap schema (C-6a): 'title' = URL (href), 'url' = Korean title (anchor text). #}
            {# english_title shown if available; fall back to Korean title (article.url col).        #}
            {# Language badge (D-19) removed per C-8 spec.                                          #}
            <li class="article-entry">
              {# P0c: category-keyed SVG thumbnail. onerror → default.svg → collapse. #}
              <img class="article-thumbnail"
                   src="assets/thumbs/{{ article.category | default('기타') | lower | replace(' ', '_') }}.svg"
                   onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='assets/thumbs/default.svg';this.onerror=function(){this.style.display='none'};"
                   alt="" width="80" height="60" loading="lazy">
              <div class="article-body">
                <a class="article-title"
                   href="{{ article.title | default('#') }}"
                   target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                  {%- if article.english_title -%}
                    {{ article.english_title }}
                  {%- else -%}
                    <span class="title-ko">{{ article.url | default("[Title unavailable]") }}</span>
                  {%- endif -%}
                </a>
                <p class="article-summary">{{ article.english_summary | default("") }}</p>
              </div>
              <div class="article-meta">
                <span class="article-meta-date">{{ article.published_date | default("") }}</span>
                {% if article.category %}
                  <span class="article-meta-category">{{ article.category }}</span>
                {% endif %}
              </div>
            </li>
          {% endfor %}
        </ul>
      {% else %}
        <div class="placeholder-card">
          <p class="placeholder-title">No relevant articles in the last 90 days.</p>
          <p class="placeholder-body">Korea deer velvet news is monitored regularly via Korean media sources.</p>
        </div>
      {% endif %}

    {% else %}
      <div class="placeholder-card">
        <p class="placeholder-title">News collection is in progress.</p>
        <p class="placeholder-body">Articles will appear after the next scheduled update.</p>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

  </section>

  {# ── SECTION 3 — IMPORT INTELLIGENCE ─────────────────────────────────── #}
  <section id="section-3">

    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-header-left">
        <h2>3. Import intelligence</h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="source-footnote">Planned: time-lag analysis comparing NZ export records (Stats NZ) with Korea import records (QIA). See sections 1 and 2 for the underlying data.</p>

    <div class="analysis-placeholder" style="margin-top:16px;">
      <p class="analysis-placeholder__title">Analysis in progress</p>
      <p class="analysis-placeholder__body">Time-lag and correlation analysis between NZ export shipments and Korea import arrivals is planned for a future update. The data shown in sections A1 and A2 provides the underlying series.</p>
    </div>

  </section>

  {# ── SECTION 4 — IMPORT RECORDS ───────────────────────────────────────── #}
  {% set import_intelligence = sections.import_intelligence if sections is defined and sections.import_intelligence is defined else {} %}
  <section id="section-4">

    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-header-left">
        <h2>4. Import records</h2>
        <span class="last-updated">Last updated: {{ import_intelligence.last_updated | default("—") }}</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="source-footnote">Source: Korea Ministry of Food and Drug Safety import notification database. Food ingredient channel.</p>

    {% if import_records_has_data %}

      <div class="table-scroll-wrapper" id="import-table-wrapper" style="margin-top:12px;">
        <table class="import-records-table" id="import-records-table">
          <caption>Korea deer velvet food import notifications</caption>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th scope="col">Date</th>
              <th scope="col">Country of origin</th>
              <th scope="col">Export country</th>
              <th scope="col">Exporter</th>
              <th scope="col">Importer</th>
              <th scope="col">Type</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody id="import-records-tbody">
            {% for row in import_records_display %}
              <tr class="import-row{% if row._in_last_90d %} row-90d{% endif %}"
                  data-date="{{ row._display_date }}"
                  style="{% if loop.index > 3 %}display:none{% endif %}">
                <td class="data">{{ row._display_date }}</td>
                <td>{{ row._display_origin }}</td>
                <td>{{ row._display_export_country }}</td>
                <td>{{ row._display_exporter }}</td>
                <td>{{ row._display_importer }}</td>
                <td>{{ row._display_type }}</td>
              </tr>
            {% endfor %}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="table-controls" id="import-table-controls">
        {# Left group: expansion controls #}
        <div style="display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <button class="show-more-btn" id="show-more-btn" type="button"
                  onclick="importShowMore(this)">Show more (in recent 90 days)</button>
          <button class="show-more-btn" id="show-fewer-btn" type="button"
                  style="display:none;"
                  onclick="importShowFewer(this)">Show fewer</button>
        </div>
        {# Right group: export controls #}
        <div style="display:flex; gap:10px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap;">
          {# CSV via email — frontend only; backend endpoint is C8-P2.
             ponytail: /api/csv-request endpoint does not exist yet — wired up in C8-P2. #}
          <button class="show-more-btn" id="csv-request-btn" type="button"
                  onclick="csvShowForm()">CSV — request by email</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      {# CSV email form (hidden until button click) #}
      <div class="csv-email-form" id="csv-email-form" aria-live="polite">
        <input type="email" id="csv-email-input" class="csv-email-input"
               placeholder="Your email address" required autocomplete="email">
        <button type="submit" class="csv-send-btn" onclick="csvSubmit()">Send CSV</button>
        <button type="button" class="csv-cancel-btn" onclick="csvCancel()">Cancel</button>
      </div>
      <div class="csv-error" id="csv-error">Request failed — please try again.</div>
      <div class="csv-confirmation" id="csv-confirmation"></div>

      <p class="table-footnote">Source: Korea Ministry of Food and Drug Safety import notification database. Importer names translated from Korean using curated lookup; exporter names appear as recorded in MFDS source data.</p>

    {% else %}
      <div class="placeholder-card" style="margin-top:16px;">
        <p class="placeholder-title">No import records available</p>
        <p class="placeholder-body">Data will appear here once the MFDS import records tab is populated.</p>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    {# Channel scope accordion #}
    <details class="discrepancy-accordion" style="margin-top:20px;">
      <summary class="discrepancy-accordion__trigger" aria-label="Why do different sources show different import volumes?">
        <span>ⓘ Why do different sources show different import volumes?</span>
        <span class="discrepancy-accordion__chevron" aria-hidden="true">&#9654;</span>
      </summary>
      <div class="discrepancy-accordion__body">
        <h4>Why the chart and table show different figures</h4>
        <p>The numbers are not directly comparable, and neither is wrong — they come from two distinct MFDS databases covering different import channels.</p>
        <p><strong>The A3 chart</strong> uses the MFDS annual statistics yearbook (식품의약품통계연보, Table 6-3-8), which records deer velvet imported as a <em>herbal medicine or pharmaceutical ingredient</em>. Figures show total annual value in USD, 2004–2024.</p>
        <p><strong>The records table</strong> uses the MFDS food-import portal (수입식품 정보마루), which records deer velvet imported as a <em>food ingredient</em>. These are individual shipment notifications filed under Korea's food safety system, 2016–2026.</p>
        <p>A third channel also exists — sliced velvet under a separate product code (HS 0507.90.1190) — which neither source covers. Total Korean deer velvet imports are therefore higher than either source shows alone.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

  </section>

  {# ── SECTION 5 — TRADE REFERENCE ─────────────────────────────────────── #}
  <section id="section-5">

    <div class="section-header">
      <div class="section-header-left">
        <h2>5. Trade reference</h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="source-footnote">Exporter guidebook produced by Deer Industry New Zealand (DINZ) for velvet exporters.</p>

    <details class="reference-accordion" style="margin-top:16px;">
      <summary>Exporter guidebook</summary>
      <div class="reference-accordion__body">
        <p>The DINZ Velvet Exporter Guidebook covers the requirements and procedures for exporting deer velvet from New Zealand to Korea and other Asian markets. It is produced by Deer Industry New Zealand for registered velvet exporters.</p>
        <p>Topics covered:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Korea import regulatory requirements and MFDS approval procedures</li>
          <li>Velvet grading and product classification standards</li>
          <li>Export documentation and customs declaration requirements</li>
          <li>Quarantine inspection and phytosanitary certificate requirements</li>
          <li>Market entry channels — pharmaceutical, food ingredient, and direct export</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="reference-download-link" href="velvet-knowledge-hub.pdf" download>Download dashboard (PDF) →</a>
      </div>
    </details>

  </section>

</main>

